Template: console-setup/codeset
Type: select
Choices: Arabic, Armenian, CyrAsia, CyrKoi, CyrSlav, Ethiopian, Georgian, Greek, Hebrew, Lao, Lat15, Lat2, Lat38, Lat7, Thai, Uni1, Uni2, Uni3, Vietnamese
Default: Uni1
Description: Which codeset is suitable for your language environment?
 Lat15 covers ISO 8859-1, ISO 8859-15 and ISO 8859-9.  Lat2 covers ISO
 8859-2, the Euro sign as well as the Romanian letters with comma
 below.  Lat38 covers ISO 8859-3 and ISO 8859-13. Lat7 covers ISO
 8859-13. CyrSlav covers not only the Slavic Cyrillic letters but also
 the Serbian Latin letters.
 .
 Uni1 supports most of the Latin languages, the Slavic Cyrillic
 languages, Hebrew and barely Arabic.  Uni2 supports most of the Latin
 languages, the Slavic Cyrillic languages and Greek.  Uni3 supports
 most of the Latin and Cyrillic languages.

